            </b><br>
            <b>What the FSD has achieved</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>Mariyaiya has delivered a thorough FSD.</b> All 20 IST
            questions are resolved. All 12 CEO-directed defects from the
            IST-3, IST-4, and PM feedback are in Section 12 as Rec 17
            through Rec 28. Each has a specific SPINRISE fix. Section
            5.5a documents the three-level approval workflow with
            Palanivel's confirmation, both web screen names, and the
            URL. Section 10 has the complete web approval screen detail.
            Section 11 includes the Pallavaa division-wise stock
            variation. The ManIndNo duplicate is confirmed and resolved.
            <b>This is the most complete FSD in the project and I
              acknowledge Mariyaiya's work.</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>Muthuvel's Sr.IST Stage 2 sign-off dated 13 April 2026 is
              properly recorded in the checklist.<br>
              <br>
            </b><br>
            <b>The problem — and it is a process problem, not a content
              problem</b><br>
            <br>
            I have reviewed both the FSD Document Identity table and the
            Review Checklist document carefully.<b> There are two
              specific issues.</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>First:</b> the TL-IST sign-off. The FSD Document Identity
            table reads: 'SIGNED OFF. TL IST: PENDING.' That is a
            contradiction in one sentence. It cannot be both signed off
            and pending. More importantly, I have checked the Review
            Checklist document you attached. The Stage 3 TL-IST section
            shows every tick box as empty and the Stage 3 sign-off box
            is completely blank — no name and no date. There is no
            evidence in either document that Palanivel has performed the
            TL-IST review.<br>
            <br>
            Your mail says 'Updated in the FSD review checklist. As
            Palanivel is on leave, I have verified and approved.'
