            TL-IST Stage 3 section is not updated. The boxes are empty
            and the sign-off is blank.<b> This statement is not accurate
              based on the document in front of me.</b><br>
            <br>
            <b>Second:</b> the PM sign-off in the FSD. The Document
            Identity table in the FSD still reads 'PENDING. PM: P.B.
            Saravanan — Stage 4 PM sign-off not yet received.' Your name
            and date are in the checklist Stage 4 sign-off box, which is
            correct. But the FSD Document Identity table, which is the
            formal record, still says PENDING. <b>Both documents must
              be consistent.</b><br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <b>Why the PM cannot substitute for TL-IST</b><br>
            <br>
            I understand the intent and I understand that Palanivel
            being on leave creates a genuine inconvenience. But the
            Stage 3 TL-IST review and the Stage 4 PM review are two
            distinct stages with two distinct purposes, and <b>neither
              can be combined into one.<br>
